@page "/how-to-play"

<div class="how-to-play">

    <h2>How to Play</h2>

    <p class="intro">
        Guess today's QSMP2 character in 6 tries.
        Each guess reveals clues about the hidden character.
    </p>

    <section>
        <h3>Clue Colors</h3>

        <div class="legend">
            <div class="legend-item">
                <span class="legend-square correct"></span>
                <div>
                    <strong>Correct</strong>
                    <p>The attribute matches exactly.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="legend-item">
                <span class="legend-square partial"></span>
                <div>
                    <strong>Close</strong>
                    <p>The attribute is related or partially matches.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="legend-item">
                <span class="legend-square wrong"></span>
                <div>
                    <strong>Incorrect</strong>
                    <p>The attribute does not match.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h3>Portrait Hints</h3>

        <p>
            The portrait becomes clearer after each guess.
            Both the portrait and the clues help identify the character.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h3>Game Modes</h3>

        <ul>
            <li><strong>Daily Mode</strong> — one shared puzzle every day.</li>
            <li><strong>Practice Mode</strong> — unlimited random characters.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h3>Tips</h3>

        <ul>
            <li>Use every clue to eliminate possibilities.</li>
            <li>Partially matching attributes can be just as valuable as exact matches.</li>
            <li>Try characters from different communities and backgrounds.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

</div>
